Manchester United are feeling the pressure as their Premier League rivals continue spending sprees aplenty, while boss Erik ten Hag is still scrambling over major signings while also battling to resolve the future of Cristiano Ronaldo. The Red Devils are still hellbent on signing Ajax ace Antony, and latest developments suggest there have been a change in heart over in Amsterdam regarding the price tag. Meanwhile, United still remain locked in an ongoing battle to secure the future of Frenkie de Jong, with the Dutch maestro weighing up his options after it became clear Barcelona and very keen to move him on in exchange for a fee. De Jong has the allure of Chelsea to contend with, and now the player's agent has spoken out to add more clarity on the situation. With the new Premier League season rapidly approaching, the time is now for United to step up and get the biggest agreements over the line. They've already landed the likes of Tyrell Malacia, Christian Eriksen and Lisandro Martinez - with the trio arriving from Feyenoord, Brentford and Ajax respectively. But after finishing sixth in the Premier League table under Ole Gunnar Solskjaer and Ralf Rangnick last term, they're on the lookout for even more reinforcements. De Jong is obviously they're top target, while Antony has been linked as well with Ten Hag on the lookout for more reinforcements. Follow all the live developments today at Old Trafford with Express Sport below